        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="761" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d761">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5151/7–1249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-12">July 12,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received July 12—11:06 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1489. PBC Nanking today adjusted US dollar official rate to PN 1,800.
                    Announcement official rate started May 16th at PN 545. Adjustments made since as
                    follows: May 20, 580; June 7th, 770; June 13th, 1200; June 14th, 1500; July 1st,
                    1600; July 9th, 1,700; July 12th, 1800.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Shanghai 832.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
